      <h1>Ionizing Bar Selection Guide for Lithium Battery Production: Complete Q&A</h1>
      <p class="blog-lead">
        Static electricity in lithium-ion battery manufacturing is a yield and safety issue in equal measure. On electrode slitting lines, unmanaged static charge causes separator puncture, dust adhesion on active material surfaces, and edge burr attraction that collectively drive defect rates well above process targets. In EV battery production, where a single micro-short circuit from a conductive particle bridging separator layers can lead to thermal runaway in the field, the consequences extend beyond factory yield into product safety. This guide addresses the specific requirements for <strong>ionizing bar</strong> deployment in lithium battery manufacturing — covering fundamentals, selection strategy, installation optimization, and fault diagnosis across all major process stages.
      </p>

